t">
    <div class=3D"rtext__content clear normal-text">
      <h2>What=E2=80=99s the Difference Between 70 (UCS-2) and 160 (GSM-7)?=
</h2>
<h3>GSM-7</h3>
<p>A text message containing text-only characters (regular letters and numb=
ers) will be encoded using GSM-7 and will have a maximum of <strong>160&nbs=
p;characters</strong>. It does not contain special characters like emojis o=
r letters with accents. If your text-only message goes over 160&nbsp;charac=
ters, it will be broken down into multiple segments.</p>
<h3>UCS-2</h3>
<p>A text message containing emojis or special characters (even just one!),=
 known as Unicode characters, (for example, =C3=80=C3=82=C3=83=C3=84=C3=87=
=C3=88=C3=89=C3=8A=C3=8B=C3=8E=C3=8F=C3=94=C3=95=C3=96=C3=99=C3=9A=C3=9B=C3=
=9C=C3=B7=C2=A9) will be encoded using UCS-2 and will have a maximum of 70&=
nbsp;characters per segment. If this type of message goes over <strong>70&n=
bsp;characters</strong>, it will be broken down into multiple segments.</p>
    </div>
   =20
  </div>

